4.00	Krasin_(1916_icebreaker)	Krasin (1916 icebreaker)	The first icebreaker Krasin (Russian: ) was built for the Imperial Russian Navy as Svyatogor. She had a long, distinguished career in rescue operations, as well as a pathfinder and explorer of the Northern Sea Route. She has been fully restored to operating condition and is now a museum ship in Saint Petersburg.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/8/82/Krasin_ice.PNG/300px-Krasin_ice.PNG
